    <h2 class="title">The Greater Vision</h2>
    <p>Institutionalize voting.</p>

    <p>UVM aleady has a handful of voting resources, but they're off the beaten path. We could move these resources into the mainstream a few ways. In the physical sense, that might look like registering voters during orientation days, while in the digital sense, it could look like a featuring of resources in the My UVM portal. Stanford even
        <a class="link" target="_blank" href="https://www.stanforddaily.com/2020/02/06/new-enrollment-hold-encourages-students-to-register-to-vote/">rolled out a system</a>
        where registering to vote is a registration-hold until you explicitly register or opt-out.</p>

    <p>It's easy to imagine how UVM supporting student voters as a core value would increase turnout.</p>
